oc:kn_55bb9f00 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After first successful compliance test" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never stop testing after the first GREEN pass. Tests passing once does NOT mean bulletproof. Continue the REFACTOR cycle until no new rationalizations emerge from multiple pressure scenarios." ;
    oc:hasRationale "First-pass compliance often breaks under different pressure combinations. Real bulletproofing requires iterating until the rationalization space is exhausted." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_5a749260 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding whether a skill needs testing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Only test skills that enforce discipline, have compliance costs, could be rationalized away, or contradict immediate goals. Do NOT test pure reference skills, skills without rules to violate, or skills agents have no incentive to bypass." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Testing is valuable only when there's a risk of non-compliance. Reference skills and low-stakes skills don't need pressure testing." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_63197052 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning skill testing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Must understand the RED-GREEN-REFACTOR TDD cycle from superpowers:test-driven-development before using this skill." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This skill provides skill-specific test formats (pressure scenarios, rationalization tables) but assumes foundational TDD knowledge." .

oc:kn_a6118f0d a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating pressure scenarios for subagent testing" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """IMPORTANT: This is a real scenario. You must choose and act.
Don't ask hypothetical questions - make the actual decision.

You have access to: [skill-being-tested]

[Concrete scenario with 3+ pressures and explicit A/B/C options]

Choose A, B, or C. Be honest.""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "The framing 'IMPORTANT: This is a real scenario' prevents agents from treating it as an academic exercise. Explicit options force a choice rather than deflection." .

oc:kn_b1cc9941 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When documenting test iterations for a skill" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Test Results: [Skill Name]
### Initial Test (Failed)
Scenario: [description]
Agent chose: [option]
Rationalization: [verbatim quote]

### Iteration N - [Change Description]
Added: [what was added]
Re-tested: Agent [chose X / still failed]
Rationalization: [verbatim quote]

### Final (Bulletproof)
Agent chose: [correct option]
Cited: [skill section]
Meta-test: [agent response]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Skill Name",
        "correct option",
        "description",
        "option",
        "verbatim quote",
        "what was added" .

oc:kn_b46dc610 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Full skill testing cycle" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. RED: Create 3+ pressure scenarios, run WITHOUT skill, document failures and rationalizations verbatim. 2. Verify RED: Identify which excuses repeat and which pressures trigger violations. 3. GREEN: Write minimal skill addressing specific baseline failures. 4. Verify GREEN: Run scenarios WITH skill, confirm compliance. 5. REFACTOR: Find new rationalizations, add explicit counters (negations + rationalization table + red flags). 6. Stay GREEN: Re-test until no new rationalizations emerge." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mirrors code TDD's RED-GREEN-REFACTOR cycle adapted for documentation testing with subagents." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_c3736a52 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "During REFACTOR phase when agent finds loopholes" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When agent violates rule despite having the skill, capture their rationalization verbatim and add three countermeasures: (1) explicit negation of that specific excuse in rules, (2) entry in rationalization table, (3) red flag list entry. Then re-test." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Generic counters like 'don't cheat' don't work. Each specific rationalization needs its own explicit negation addressing the exact wording agents use." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ca515007 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing pressure scenarios for skill testing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never test skills with academic scenarios that lack pressure. Bad: 'You need to implement a feature. What does the skill say?' Good: Concrete scenarios with 3+ combined pressures (time + sunk cost + exhaustion) forcing explicit A/B/C choices." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Agents resist single pressure easily but break under multiple combined pressures. Academic scenarios cause agents to recite the skill without testing actual compliance." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_e3cea9d4 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before writing or editing any skill" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If you didn't watch an agent fail without the skill, you don't know if the skill prevents the right failures. Always run baseline (RED) scenarios BEFORE writing the skill." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without observing actual failure modes, you only address what you THINK needs preventing, not what ACTUALLY needs preventing." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_e3f7695c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating whether testing is complete" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A skill is bulletproof when: (1) agent chooses correct option under maximum pressure, (2) agent cites skill sections as justification, (3) agent acknowledges temptation but follows rule anyway, (4) meta-testing reveals 'skill was clear, I should follow it'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These four signals together confirm the skill is genuinely effective, not just superficially compliant." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_fee62fec a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When agent fails pressure test despite having the skill" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use meta-testing when GREEN isn't working: after agent chooses wrong option, ask how the skill could have been written differently. Three outcomes: (1) 'skill was clear' → add foundational principle, (2) 'skill should have said X' → documentation problem, add suggestion, (3) 'didn't see section Y' → organization problem, make key points prominent." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Meta-testing distinguishes between documentation problems, organization problems, and foundational principle gaps, each requiring different fixes." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

